==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Saxicavous
<hw>Sax`i*ca"vous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>saxum</ets> rock + <ets>cavare</ets> to make hollow, fr.
<ets>cavus</ets> hollow: cf. F. <ets>saxicave</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Boring, or hollowing out, rocks; -- said of
certain mollusks which live in holes which they burrow in
rocks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saxicoline</ent>⟦br⟧
